page.title: 10WOODLAND
page.content: A mainly rural square covered by grassland with thorn hedges separating fields.Small concentrations of woodland are also a feature especially near Rottington and along stretches of minor roads.Rottington Hall farm is the biggest in the square with Byersteads farm the only other feature worthy of note.It is interesting to note that the name Rottington is supposed to have derived its name fron a Viking chief who settled in the area.Some locals believe that it is here that St.Bega built her nunnery and not St.Bees.However, until now no definite evidence exists.
